## 1. How do you deploy an Amazon EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service) cluster?

I deploy an EKS cluster using either **eksctl**, **Terraform**, or AWS Console, depending on the environment.

### Using eksctl (most common method)

eksctl create cluster \
  --name my-cluster \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --nodegroup-name workers \
  --node-type t3.medium \
  --nodes 2

### Deployment Steps:
- Create VPC and networking components
- Create EKS control plane
- Create managed or self-managed node group
- Configure kubectl using:
  aws eks update-kubeconfig
- Verify cluster:
  kubectl get nodes

### Best Practices:
- Use private subnets for worker nodes
- Enable IAM Roles for Service Accounts (IRSA)
- Enable control plane logging

